Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.60,0:02:23.16,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,So you've brought her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.09,0:02:50.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,K-Kagome...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.08,0:03:05.41,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I did it!\NI win.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.54,0:03:06.37,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Banzai!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.45,0:03:07.47,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,- Banzai!\N- Wrong one...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.55,0:03:09.10,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You're really good, Kagome.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.18,0:03:11.24,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Miroku, I'm disappointed in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.85,0:03:15.12,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,These {\i1}karuta{\i0} cards are so fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.39,0:03:18.62,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,They're not {\i1}karuta.{\i0}\NWe call it trumps. (playing cards)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.29,0:03:21.26,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Torampu?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.33,0:03:23.69,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Trumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.76,0:03:25.70,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Cut out the racket!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.23,0:03:28.70,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Can't you play quietly?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.97,0:03:30.90,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Say Inuyasha, come and join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.97,0:03:32.96,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Not interested!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:35.50,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Why's he so angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.11,0:03:37.54,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,He's in a bad mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.71,0:03:38.73,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.91,0:03:41.68,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Sulking won't make\NTetsusaiga any stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.75,0:03:44.48,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shaddup! I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.15,0:03:46.67,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Naraku's barrier...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:52.66,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Until he's able to break the barrier,\nwe can't even touch Naraku.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.03,0:03:55.58,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wind Scar!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.77,0:04:06.26,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Wind Scar had no effect.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.97,0:04:08.37,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}I told you...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.47,0:04:11.03,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}I continue to grow stronger.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.28,0:04:14.34,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's a problem, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.25,0:04:19.41,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Hah! No need to worry.\NI'll take care of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.69,0:04:21.55,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What'll you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.69,0:04:23.85,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Have you any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.93,0:04:31.16,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Knew it! You haven't got a clue!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.66,0:04:33.06,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shouldn't have gotten\nmy hopes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.60,0:04:34.59,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Hey you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.67,0:04:36.16,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.24,0:04:37.10,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.61,0:04:40.90,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.94,0:04:43.37,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Old Myoga...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:48.51,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I know how to handle\NNaraku's barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.85,0:04:50.14,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You know something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.32,0:04:53.81,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I hurried over just to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.95,0:04:54.92,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.02,0:04:57.75,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And I'll let you suck all the blood\nyou want outta Kagome.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.89,0:04:59.65,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Why me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.39,0:05:03.99,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This is no time for jokes, Inuyasha.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.23,0:05:07.69,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You must go immediately to\nthe nest of the Demon Bats.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.70,0:05:10.33,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Demon Bats?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.30,0:05:13.79,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Near a village on the\nwestern shores
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.87,0:05:16.50,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,is the nest of the\NDemon Bat Tribe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.11,0:05:20.01,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The nest is protected by\nan impenetrable barrier
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.11,0:05:21.98,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,and no one is able\nto destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.45,0:05:24.31,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The guardianship of the\nbarrier is passed down
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.38,0:05:25.58,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,from generation to generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.98,0:05:29.68,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You must kill this\nguardian demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.03,0:05:38.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,To put it plainly,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.16,0:05:41.56,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,kill the demon guardian who\nhas the power to put up this barrier
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.63,0:05:44.47,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,and let Tetsusaiga absorb\nits blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.04,0:05:47.70,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,By killing a strong opponent,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.77,0:05:50.11,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Tetsusaiga will synergize\nhis power?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.54,0:05:52.94,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And make Tetsusaiga stronger?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.98,0:05:55.67,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.05,0:05:58.38,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Now then.\NKagome, your blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.45,0:06:02.72,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Awright then, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.19,0:06:04.59,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Demon-hunting, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.66,0:06:07.65,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If that's all it takes\nto make Tetsusaiga stronger,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.93,0:06:10.29,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'll kill a hundred,\neven a thousand of 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.31,0:06:26.14,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You lied to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.75,0:06:30.51,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You said if you gave your\ndaughter to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.58,0:06:33.05,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Our village wouldn't\nbe attacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:33.91,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Well?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.29,0:06:36.31,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,More villagers have\nbeen killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.39,0:06:37.88,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,That's not what you promised!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.96,0:06:40.02,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Why'd they attack us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.56,0:06:43.59,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,She's probably one of them...\none of those Demon Bats!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.66,0:06:46.53,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Yeah! Show no mercy!\NLet her have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.97,0:06:53.84,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,H-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.44,0:06:59.21,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,W-Who're you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.78,0:07:01.75,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You mentioned Demon Bats\njust now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.65,0:07:04.98,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Tell me where their nest is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.92,0:07:07.01,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.32,0:07:10.15,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,How dare you attack\na woman like that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.92,0:07:14.05,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,As if {\i1}we{\i0} would know\nwhere the nest is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.26,0:07:15.82,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Ask that woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.06,0:07:19.00,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,She's a rotten bitch who\ncalls herself human,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.23,0:07:22.63,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,but bore the child\nof a Demon Bat!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.67,0:07:26.90,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}The child of a demon?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.81,0:07:37.31,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Why do you want to know\nwhere the nest is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.75,0:07:38.94,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.25,0:07:40.68,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm gonna destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:42.02,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.42,0:07:44.51,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Inuyasha.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.96,0:07:48.41,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You said you gave your child\nto the Demon Bats.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.49,0:07:49.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:54.06,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The Demon Bats have always\nlived in this region.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:57.43,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,They prey on humans and animals\nand suck out their blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.50,0:07:59.30,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,they're frightening demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.70,0:08:02.14,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But Tsukuyomaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.24,0:08:07.68,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,My daughter's father, Tsukuyomaru,\nwas different.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.65,0:08:10.95,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,He did not kill humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.38,0:08:12.91,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And after Shiori was born,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.98,0:08:15.04,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I don't know if he convinced\nthe other Demon Bats,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.12,0:08:17.92,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,but they stopped attacking\nOur village.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.16,0:08:27.65,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, Our village was at peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.40,0:08:29.33,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Was?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.14,0:08:31.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Tsukuyomaru died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:34.41,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And there was no one\nto stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:38.40,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Aghh! The Demon Bats!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.32,0:08:52.45,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Soon after, Tsukuyomaru's father,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.52,0:08:55.29,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Taigokumaru, who is Shiori's grandfather,\ncame to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:09:00.42,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If I handed Shiori over to him,\nhe promised to leave our village alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:04.63,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Taigokumaru and Tsukuyomaru\nwere guardians of the barrier,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.70,0:09:06.97,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,a duty passed down from\ngeneration to generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.84,0:09:12.28,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And Shiori, as Tsukuyomaru's daughter,\nwas needed to carry on the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.85,0:09:19.44,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Why did it have to be Shiori?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.82,0:09:23.65,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If this Taigokumaru had\nthe guardian power...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.99,0:09:25.48,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Power wanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:30.92,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And once one passes on\nhis duty, he loses the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.20,0:09:33.19,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,In other words, Shiori is\nthe only one remaining
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.27,0:09:36.03,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,who has the power to\nprotect the barrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.91,0:09:43.53,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hah! Hah! Demon child!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.61,0:09:46.01,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Half-demon! Half-demon!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.50,0:10:11.83,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm home, Mommy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.60,0:10:16.51,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shiori! How'd you get\nthose scratches on your face?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.34,0:10:20.74,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's nothing. I just fell.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.12,0:10:27.28,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's the matter?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.29,0:10:30.69,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}I just fell, I said.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.86,0:10:32.85,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm so sorry!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.27,0:10:43.53,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I agonized over this,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:44.76,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,but in the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.84,0:10:46.70,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I gave up my Shiori\nto Taigokumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.81,0:10:53.57,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,So you've brought her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.91,0:10:54.88,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,As I promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.95,0:10:58.61,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,In return, never attack\nOur village again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.15,0:11:01.38,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes, I give you my word.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.92,0:11:03.65,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Now Shiori, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.99,0:11:07.32,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I changed my mind.\NI'm afraid of Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.56,0:11:09.12,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Please go, Shiori!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.66,0:11:10.89,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,For the sake of the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.27,0:11:14.46,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.97,0:11:20.30,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Forgive me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.61,0:11:23.84,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}You'll be happier\nover there.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.78,0:11:30.01,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Pardon my asking, but\NShiori is half-demon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.45,0:11:33.38,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Would a half-demon child\nhave such powers?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.05,0:11:36.42,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,From the looks of it,\nyou are also a half-demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.06,0:11:40.39,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Then you understand that just\nbecause you're half a demon doesn't mean
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.46,0:11:42.52,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,you're accepted by the demon world,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.59,0:11:44.89,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,nor does it mean you're\nembraced by humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:49.36,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Well, Inuyasha?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.67,0:11:51.23,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.24,0:11:55.54,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shiori had ample power to\nfulfill her duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.97,0:11:56.91,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.41,0:12:00.34,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I thought it was for her good\nto go to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:03.64,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And if that would save\nthe village, I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.82,0:12:08.55,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But the Demon Bats went\nagainst their word.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.06,0:12:15.53,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,- Take me there.\N- Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.80,0:12:20.46,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Take me to that old man,\nwhatever his name is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.80,0:12:22.10,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Then we'll go, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.17,0:12:23.76,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,No! I'll be fine alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.10,0:12:24.93,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.14,0:12:28.37,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm the one who has\nbusiness with 'im.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.60,0:13:33.73,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Penny for your thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.91,0:13:35.67,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I was thinking back...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.64,0:13:39.37,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Old Myoga!\NWhy'd you follow me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.48,0:13:42.04,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And why not?\NI won't be in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.78,0:13:46.11,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I told you not to come!\NGo back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.18,0:13:47.71,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Don't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.79,0:13:48.58,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.22,0:13:52.69,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Let us go, Inuyasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.13,0:13:55.49,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Do as you please!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.87,0:14:05.84,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.00,0:14:06.73,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.81,0:14:09.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I cannot have you\nstarving to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.02,0:14:24.68,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,That cave over yonder.\NWhere it glows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.66,0:14:30.25,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh? Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.76,0:14:31.63,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shiori!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.03,0:14:35.16,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Myoga...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.63,0:14:38.57,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You sure about this?\NThe way to make Tetsusaiga stronger?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.30,0:14:43.04,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Yes... You must kill that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.45,0:14:53.35,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shiori! Shiori!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.35,0:14:56.05,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.79,0:15:01.49,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I wondered what\nthe ruckus was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.56,0:15:03.58,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It seems we have visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.27,0:15:11.39,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Is he the one?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.47,0:15:12.60,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Taigokumaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.11,0:15:18.77,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You tricked me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.11,0:15:21.60,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Hmm? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.81,0:15:25.54,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You promised to leave the\nvillage alone in return for Shiori!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:26.81,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.22,0:15:32.12,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You really believed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.39,0:15:38.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,As if a demon would really\nkeep a promise to a human!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.16,0:15:40.29,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Then return Shiori to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.70,0:15:41.53,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Mommy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.60,0:15:42.83,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I will not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.90,0:15:47.03,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Shiori will be the guardian of\nthe barrier for the rest of her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:51.30,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,She inherited the duty from her\nlate father, Tsukuyomaru,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.38,0:15:53.81,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,and she is doing a fine job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.28,0:15:58.15,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe that she\nhas a human for a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.62,0:16:03.61,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Hey lady, I think the only way to get\nyour daughter back is through force.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.82,0:16:06.02,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Force? Can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.49,0:16:10.39,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,That cocky, old bat... He's standing\nin front of Shiori.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.10,0:16:11.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If I attack now,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.93,0:16:15.63,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I can get him\nwithout hurting Shiori.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.90,0:16:22.81,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Wind... Scar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.95,0:16:29.64,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.15,0:16:34.24,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,He repelled my Wind Scar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.79,0:16:38.42,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Oh dear! The barrier of the Demon Bat\nis to be feared!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.49,0:16:40.75,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Rumor was right about\nit being impenetrable!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.69,0:16:44.06,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Just who are you, kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.26,0:16:46.29,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter who I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.56,0:16:48.53,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Give Shiori back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.73,0:16:52.17,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I see... So the mortals sent you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.67,0:16:55.14,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Well, you can die here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.25,0:17:08.08,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I won't miss this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.09,0:17:12.61,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Why you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.73,0:17:15.95,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.73,0:17:18.92,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Please stop, Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.56,0:17:21.59,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Please don't hurt Mommy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.93,0:17:24.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'll work hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.87,0:17:25.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,So please...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:28.41,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Please don't hurt Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.94,0:17:34.17,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.35,0:17:38.18,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This child has far more\nsense than you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.65,0:17:41.02,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Why you! Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.22,0:17:42.55,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Let me ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.62,0:17:46.49,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Do you think Shiori will be\nhappy back in the village?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.72,0:17:47.55,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.89,0:17:49.19,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I know it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.26,0:17:53.92,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,The villagers ostracized her\nbecause Shiori is a half-demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.60,0:17:57.19,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And because they valued\ntheir lives more,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.27,0:17:59.74,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,they didn't hesitate for a second and\noffered Shiori to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.80,0:18:04.30,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,How can I return my dear granddaughter\nto such selfish villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.49,0:18:19.72,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It didn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.22,0:18:22.22,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'll resign myself to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.63,0:18:23.56,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.76,0:18:27.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What Taigokumaru said\nwas true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.33,0:18:30.23,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,This village didn't accept\nme or Shiori.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.47,0:18:32.06,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Maybe she's better off there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.14,0:18:33.73,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Hah! You're so naïve.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.87,0:18:34.57,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.21,0:18:39.58,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Demons never accept half-demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.11,0:18:42.71,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Even if they're blood kin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.38,0:18:48.08,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'm a fine demon.\NAnd I accept you, Inuyasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.15,0:18:49.21,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.29,0:18:52.59,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Isn't it only 'cuz\NI protect you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.06,0:18:56.03,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Anyway, as long as Inuyasha cannot\nbreak the barrier,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.09,0:18:57.32,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,nothing can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.40,0:18:59.83,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,And didn't we come here\nbecause of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.90,0:19:02.26,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Hah! I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.60,0:19:05.97,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kill a half-demon who guards\na strong barrier...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.04,0:19:08.34,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}and let Tetsusaiga absorb\nhis blood.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.44,0:19:10.30,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then Tetsusaiga would grow\nin power{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.37,0:19:12.54,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}and be able to break\nthrough Naraku's barrier.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.51,0:19:14.41,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}But...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.58,0:19:19.31,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}No way can Inuyasha kill\nthe half-demon.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.82,0:19:21.44,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's just a little girl.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.66,0:19:28.02,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mommy...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.26,0:19:29.42,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}I want to see you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.70,0:19:32.75,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}If only Father were alive...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.33,0:19:35.36,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why did he have to die?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.87,0:19:47.00,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I guess she misses her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.78,0:19:53.55,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,If this keeps up, there's no telling when\nshe'll ask to go back to the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.05,0:19:57.11,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Then... I will make them disappear...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.19,0:20:00.89,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Your village and your mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.30,0:20:07.20,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:38.12,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Half-demon?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.41,0:20:50.70,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mother... What is a half-demon?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.62,0:20:58.64,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.98,0:20:59.85,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.62,0:21:01.59,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It's you, Kagome.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.72,0:21:06.28,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Thinking about Shiori?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.02,0:21:08.32,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Not only that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.66,0:21:10.35,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,You're so kind, Inuyasha.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:12.86,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Stupid! I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.63,0:21:16.29,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,It must've been hard for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.34,0:21:19.90,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I probably couldn't imagine\nthe hardship...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:24.70,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But you know, Inuyasha?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.78,0:21:25.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.01,0:21:29.31,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,No, not only me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.55,0:21:33.45,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But even Miroku, Sango,\NShippo and Myoga...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.52,0:21:34.61,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.99,0:21:41.12,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Good boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.69,0:21:44.13,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Oww! Don't treat me like a dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.36,0:21:47.09,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.23,0:21:49.49,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.30,0:21:52.96,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Huh? That's!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.01,0:22:00.94,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,A whole colony of Demon Bats!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.15,0:23:51.35,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,I'll work hard as the\nguardian of the barrier,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.42,0:23:54.22,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,so please spare Mommy and\nthe villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.66,0:23:57.25,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Little Shiori-\NSo young, yet so diligent!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.33,0:23:59.35,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,But unless Inuyasha kills this\ninnocent child,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.43,0:24:01.59,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Tetsusaiga can't increase its power!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.27,0:24:04.29,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,How can Inuyasha do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.37,0:24:05.20,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.27,0:24:06.96,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,There's just one way!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.11,0:24:11.80,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Next on Inuyasha:\N"The Red Tetsusaiga Breaks the Barrier!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.98,0:24:14.84,Style1,Comment,0,0,0,,Inuyasha's concern transforms Tetsusaiga!
